  "text": "To determine if this increase in cell-cell fusion in cells overexpressing ERdj5 or PDI protein was due directly to the increased production of free thiols, we characterized the effect of an inhibitor of free thiols on cytoplasmic content mixing in cells overexpressing ERdj5 or PDI proteins. DTNB, a nonspecific inhibitor of free thiols [CITATION_1] , efficiently inhibited the content mixing in cells overexpressing ERdj5 or PDI protein as well as in cells expressing NDV glycoproteins alone (Fig. 3A) . This result showed that the increased fusion also was dependent on thiol isomerase activity.",
